<!--
  L1 daily tasks: HiWi work.

  AspirationCareer's display name/description live under an `_display_data`
  variant in EA's TDESC, not at root; EA's own AspirationCareer goldens omit
  them entirely (e.g. aspiration_Culinary_Level5). The player sees the level
  title from the parent CareerLevel's `title`/`title_description`.

  aspiration_valid_age_type — closes issue #22. The career panel widget
  (SimInfoCareerPanelMain.RefreshPanelHeightRange) walks
    CareerLevel.aspiration -> AspirationCareer.objectives
  to render the expanded "daily tasks" rows. EA's runtime gates references
  to Aspiration-derived classes through `Aspiration.is_valid_for_sim`,
  which evaluates `sim_info.age & self.aspiration_valid_age_type`. The TDESC
  declares `parents=AspirationBasic` for AspirationCareer, suggesting the
  field is inert here, but EA's Python class hierarchy diverges from the
  TDESC: `AspirationCareer` inherits the validity gate at runtime, and an
  unset (or `INVALID=0`) age-type silently fails the AND, leaving the
  panel's resolved aspiration ref null. The CareerCellView expander then
  reads an empty objectives array and `array[0]` throws Error #1125 ("the
  index 0 is out of range 0"). Same enum-fallback bug family as #17 (which
  fixed it for the CAS-side aspiration tiers); the career-side
  AspirationCareer instances need the same explicit value. CAS visits make
  the bug deterministic because the post-CAS reload re-runs the runtime
  validity gate (pre-CAS the panel may use a cached non-null ref). See
  Docs/NOTE_aspiration_track_registration.md for the load-time trace of
  the enum-fallback mechanism. Historian is YA/Adult/Elder gameplay, but
  TEEN_OR_OLDER (= TEEN|YA|ADULT|ELDER = 120) is the only multi-age
  member EA ships; the career_availablity_tests on the Career enforce the
  real gating (YA/A/E).
-->
<I c="AspirationCareer" i="aspiration" m="aspirations.aspiration_tuning" n="aspiration_career_Historian_L1" s="TBD_INSTANCE_ID">
  <E n="aspiration_valid_age_type">TEEN_OR_OLDER</E>
  <L n="objectives">
    <T>objective_HC_RunTranscribeManuscript_x2</T>
    <T>objective_HC_ReadNonfictionBook</T>
  </L>
</I>
